{"parents": [], "prev": {"link": "../15-bitlevels/", "title": "Multi-tiered bitlevel systems"}, "next": {"link": "../17-shutdown/", "title": "Shutting down gracefully"}, "title": "Adding hardcoded modules", "meta": null, "body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"adding-hardcoded-modules\">\n<h1>Adding hardcoded modules<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#adding-hardcoded-modules\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p>RhostMUSH does support module writing.</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"modifying-sourcode-to-add-a-module\">\n<h2>Modifying sourcode to add a module<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#modifying-sourcode-to-add-a-module\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>This requires hooking your changes into local.c, then modifying the Makefile (in the src directory)\nfor any new source files that you wish to add.</p>\n<p>Something to be aware of is that all localized data is ran after the system cache subroutine.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"adding-an-startup-to-make-use-of-modules\">\n<h2>Adding an &#64;startup to make use of modules<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#adding-an-startup-to-make-use-of-modules\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>This means that if your code is depending on &#64;startups, you need to put a delay in the &#64;startup\nso that your local code can be loaded in as modules prior to the &#64;startup execution.</p>\n<p>Something that will not work:</p>\n<p>&#64;startup <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"mailto:me=&#37;&#52;&#48;superhappyfuncommand\">me=<span>&#64;</span>superhappyfuncommand</a> loadmeup=now</p>\n<p>A small alteration that will likely make this work fine.</p>\n<p>&#64;startup <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"mailto:me=&#37;&#52;&#48;wait\">me=<span>&#64;</span>wait</a> <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"mailto:1=&#37;&#52;&#48;superhappyfuncommand\">1=<span>&#64;</span>superhappyfuncommand</a> loadmeup=now</p>\n<p>That 1 second delay for the queue will give the game engine time to load in your module code.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"contributing-your-module-back-to-rhost\">\n<h2>Contributing your module back to Rhost<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#contributing-your-module-back-to-rhost\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>If you wish your modules to be part of the main Rhost distribution you have two options:</p>\n<ol class=\"arabic simple\">\n<li><p>Attempt to hack the bin/asksource.sh and bin/asksource.blank files.</p></li>\n<li><p>Ask one of the Rhost devs to do it for you :)</p></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n", "metatags": "", "rellinks": [["genindex", "General Index", "I", "index"], ["17-shutdown", "Shutting down gracefully", "N", "next"], ["15-bitlevels", "Multi-tiered bitlevel systems", "P", "previous"]], "sourcename": "16-modules.rst.txt", "toc": "<ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#\">Adding hardcoded modules</a><ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#modifying-sourcode-to-add-a-module\">Modifying sourcode to add a module</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#adding-an-startup-to-make-use-of-modules\">Adding an &#64;startup to make use of modules</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#contributing-your-module-back-to-rhost\">Contributing your module back to Rhost</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n", "display_toc": true, "page_source_suffix": ".rst", "current_page_name": "16-modules", "sidebars": ["localtoc.html", "relations.html", "sourcelink.html", "searchbox.html"], "customsidebar": null, "alabaster_version": "0.7.12", "insegel_version": "1.1.0"}